message.text:
「もういくつ寝ると～、２０１５年～♪」

2014年も残すところあとわずか！
今年も振り返ってみると、多くの方に支えられ、たくさんの笑顔をいただいた１年でした。
国際交流基金一同、心から感謝しております。

皆さんにとってはどんな１年でしたか？？
食べすぎ飲みすぎには注意して、皆さん良いお年をお過ごしください！

Count down to new year 2015!
Thank you so much for all your support and smiles this year.

Wishing you all the very best wishes for the new year!
Be careful not to eat too much during the holidays!　
Yoi Otoshi Wo!

message.text:
WASABI's concerts in Beijing (1/5) and Shanghai (1/8) 2015!!
 http://www.jpf.go.jp/j/cult…/perform/oversea/1412/12-02.html
新・純邦楽ユニット「WASABI」　中国巡回公演（1/5北京、1/8上海）

When you hear "WASABI", what comes to your mind first??
 Maybe the greenish strong-flavored plant which is often eaten with sushi??

 Today, let us recommend you "WASABI", the Japanese band with four talented players: Ryoichiro Yoshida on Tsugaru-shamisen (three-stringed Japanese guitar), Hiromu Motonaga on Shakuhachi (bamboo flute), Shin Ichikawa on Koto (Japanese harp) and Naosaburou Bihou on Taiko (Japanese drum).

 The name "WASABI" combines the two elements "Wa（和）", meaning Japanese, and "Sabi（サビ）", referring to the catchy part of a song.

 Although their instruments are all Japanese traditional ones, WASABI's music succeeds in producing not only traditional elegance but also a new groove, which makes them highly rated as "Neo-traditional" band.

 Check their performance and feel the powerful sounds!! >> https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F0sXp9yAAPg&list=UUWNkrzmC1XpWFCDBDs2dShA

今年度から開始した「文化庁　東アジア文化交流使」に任命されたWASABIが2015年新春、北京と上海で公演します。
 迫力ある「和のバンド」のグルーヴをお楽しみくださいっ！
※今公演は吉田良一郎氏（三味線）が怪我のため、代演として吉田兄弟(弟)　吉田健一氏の参加となります。

 写真：WASABI（左から：市川慎、元永拓、美鵬直三朗、吉田良一郎）／吉田健一

message.text:
<KANJI Quiz!>
How do you read the Kanji "窓"(window)？ Choose the answer!
1. あたま（atama) 2. まど(mado) 3. さわぐ(sawagu)
http://www.anime-manga.jp/KanjiGame/School/

Today is "TOJI" （とうじ、冬至）, winter solstice,
a day when the northern hemisphere experiences its shortest
day time and longest night of the year!

BESIDES! This year has a very special type of Toji called "Sakutan Toji (さくたんとうじ、朔旦冬至)". Sakutan Toji is a day when new moon coincidentally falls on the winter solstice day which only comes once in nineteen years. As it is a very rare day, Sakutan Toji is considered to be very auspicious! 

Why don't you look outside the "窓 (window)" and feel the longest night today?

「窓」の読み方はどれ？今日12月22日は「冬至（とうじ）」です！

冬至は１年で１番昼が短く、夜が長い日。しかも！今年は19年に１度の新月と重なる「朔旦冬至（さくたんとうじ）」と呼ばれる特別な冬至で、縁起がよいとされています。
今日は「窓」の外をみて、一番長い夜を感じてみませんか？
